03577nam a22005175i 9780226251745DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20092008ilu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802262517457 a10.7208/97802262517452doi  a(DE-B1597)524837  a(OCoLC)812509463  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ailucUS-IL 4aBM602b.F57 2010 7aREL0000002bisacsh04a296.32221 aFishbane, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aSacred Attunement :bA Jewish Theology /cMichael Fishbane. 1aChicago : bUniversity of Chicago Press, c[2009] 4c©2008  a1 online resource (246 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- t1. Toward Theology -- t2. A Jewish Hermeneutical Theology -- t3. Religious Practice and Forms of Attention -- t4. Forms of Thought and Living Theology -- tEpilogue -- tAcknowledgments -- tNotes -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aContemporary theology, and Jewish theology in particular, Michael Fishbane asserts, now lies fallow, beset by strong critiques from within and without. For Jewish reality, a coherent and wide-ranging response in thoroughly modern terms is needed. Sacred Attunement is Fishbane’s attempt to renew Jewish theology for our time, in the larger context of modern and postmodern challenges to theology and theological thought in the broadest sense. The first part of the book regrounds theology in this setting and opens up new pathways through nature, art, and the theological dimension as a whole. In the second section, Fishbane introduces his hermeneutical theology—one grounded in the interpretation of scripture as a distinctly Jewish practice. The third section focuses on modes of self-cultivation for awakening and sustaining a covenant theology. The final section takes up questions of scripture, authority, belief, despair, and obligation as theological topics in their own right. The first full-scale Jewish theology in America since Abraham J. Heschel’s God in Search of Man and the first comprehensive Jewish philosophical theology since Franz Rosenzweig’s Star of Redemption, Sacred Attunement is a work of uncommon personal integrity and originality from one of the most distinguished scholars of Judaica in our time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aHermeneuticsxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 0aJudaismxDoctrines. 0aSpiritual lifexJudaism. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226251745423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226251745.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles